<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Size 0.6-0.9 mm. Body as common for 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borner &amp; June" authorityYear="1901" lsidName="" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Anurophorinae">Anurophorinae</taxonomicName>
with short furca (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 27–31" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figures 27 - 31. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 27 appearance 28 furcal area, lateral view 29 furca, posterior view 30 tibiotarsus of Leg 3, outer view 31 ventral side of Th. II and Abd. I and II. Abbreviations: vmc-ventro-medial setae." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures27-31" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412378" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">27</figureCitation>
). Pigmentation grey, as in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Tullberg" baseAuthorityYear="1871" class="Collembola" family="Isotomidae" genus="Proisotoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Proisotoma minuta" order="Entomobryomorpha" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minuta">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Proisotoma minuta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Tullberg, 1871). Cuticle finely reticulated, size of largest polygons smaller than bases of setae. Ocelli 8+8, G and H smaller (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 19 s-, ms-setae, macrosetae, and p-rows of setae on body tergites 20 chaetotaxy of Abd. III-VI 21 labial papilla E 22 Ant. 3, dorso-lateral view 23 ommatidia and Ant. 1 24 - 26 apex of Ant. 4, lateral (24), dorsal (25), and ventro-lateral (26) views. Abbreviations: bms-basal micro s-seta, ab-apical bulb, ms-micro s-seta, org-organite, s-s-seta, is, ls, os-inner, lateral, and outer s-setae of antennal organ." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412377" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23</figureCitation>
), all ocelli usually look subequal by pigmentation. PAO with three guard setae along posterior margin, elliptical, not constricted, as long as 0.4-0.6 of Ant.1 width and 0.7-1.1 as long as U3 (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 19 s-, ms-setae, macrosetae, and p-rows of setae on body tergites 20 chaetotaxy of Abd. III-VI 21 labial papilla E 22 Ant. 3, dorso-lateral view 23 ommatidia and Ant. 1 24 - 26 apex of Ant. 4, lateral (24), dorsal (25), and ventro-lateral (26) views. Abbreviations: bms-basal micro s-seta, ab-apical bulb, ms-micro s-seta, org-organite, s-s-seta, is, ls, os-inner, lateral, and outer s-setae of antennal organ." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412377" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23</figureCitation>
). Maxillary outer lobe with simple maxillary palp and four sublobal hairs. Labral formula as 2/554. Labium with all papillae (A-E), papillae A-D with normal number of guards (1,4,0,4), E with four guards (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 19 s-, ms-setae, macrosetae, and p-rows of setae on body tergites 20 chaetotaxy of Abd. III-VI 21 labial papilla E 22 Ant. 3, dorso-lateral view 23 ommatidia and Ant. 1 24 - 26 apex of Ant. 4, lateral (24), dorsal (25), and ventro-lateral (26) views. Abbreviations: bms-basal micro s-seta, ab-apical bulb, ms-micro s-seta, org-organite, s-s-seta, is, ls, os-inner, lateral, and outer s-setae of antennal organ." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412377" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">21</figureCitation>
). Main part of labium with three proximal, four basomedian and five basolateral setae. Ventral side of head with 4+4 postlabial setae. Ant.1 with two basal, ventral and dorsal, bms, two ventro-lateral s, and eleven setae, without p-setae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 19 s-, ms-setae, macrosetae, and p-rows of setae on body tergites 20 chaetotaxy of Abd. III-VI 21 labial papilla E 22 Ant. 3, dorso-lateral view 23 ommatidia and Ant. 1 24 - 26 apex of Ant. 4, lateral (24), dorsal (25), and ventro-lateral (26) views. Abbreviations: bms-basal micro s-seta, ab-apical bulb, ms-micro s-seta, org-organite, s-s-seta, is, ls, os-inner, lateral, and outer s-setae of antennal organ." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412377" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">23</figureCitation>
). Ant.2 with three bms and one laterodistal s. Ant.3 without bms and with five distal s (including one lateral spine-like), inner s of AO small (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 19 s-, ms-setae, macrosetae, and p-rows of setae on body tergites 20 chaetotaxy of Abd. III-VI 21 labial papilla E 22 Ant. 3, dorso-lateral view 23 ommatidia and Ant. 1 24 - 26 apex of Ant. 4, lateral (24), dorsal (25), and ventro-lateral (26) views. Abbreviations: bms-basal micro s-seta, ab-apical bulb, ms-micro s-seta, org-organite, s-s-seta, is, ls, os-inner, lateral, and outer s-setae of antennal organ." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412377" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">22</figureCitation>
). All s-setae on Ant.1-3 very short. S-setae on Ant.4 weakly differentiated, subapical organite small. Apex of Ant.4 with bilobed bulb (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 19 s-, ms-setae, macrosetae, and p-rows of setae on body tergites 20 chaetotaxy of Abd. III-VI 21 labial papilla E 22 Ant. 3, dorso-lateral view 23 ommatidia and Ant. 1 24 - 26 apex of Ant. 4, lateral (24), dorsal (25), and ventro-lateral (26) views. Abbreviations: bms-basal micro s-seta, ab-apical bulb, ms-micro s-seta, org-organite, s-s-seta, is, ls, os-inner, lateral, and outer s-setae of antennal organ." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412377" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">24-26</figureCitation>
), well visible in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 19 s-, ms-setae, macrosetae, and p-rows of setae on body tergites 20 chaetotaxy of Abd. III-VI 21 labial papilla E 22 Ant. 3, dorso-lateral view 23 ommatidia and Ant. 1 24 - 26 apex of Ant. 4, lateral (24), dorsal (25), and ventro-lateral (26) views. Abbreviations: bms-basal micro s-seta, ab-apical bulb, ms-micro s-seta, org-organite, s-s-seta, is, ls, os-inner, lateral, and outer s-setae of antennal organ." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412377" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">25</figureCitation>
). In fully grown animals the bulb can look trilobed due to slight secondary division of one of the lobes (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 19–26" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figures 19 - 26. Ephemerotoma buryatica sp. nov. 19 s-, ms-setae, macrosetae, and p-rows of setae on body tergites 20 chaetotaxy of Abd. III-VI 21 labial papilla E 22 Ant. 3, dorso-lateral view 23 ommatidia and Ant. 1 24 - 26 apex of Ant. 4, lateral (24), dorsal (25), and ventro-lateral (26) views. Abbreviations: bms-basal micro s-seta, ab-apical bulb, ms-micro s-seta, org-organite, s-s-seta, is, ls, os-inner, lateral, and outer s-setae of antennal organ." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.935.49363.figures19-26" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/412377" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">26</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
